HEADWORD: Osteomalacia
<hw>Os`te*o*ma*la"ci*a</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[NL.,
fr. Gr. <grk>'oste`on</grk> bone + <?/ softness.]</ety>
<fld>(Med.)</fld> <def>A disease of the bones, in which they lose their
earthy material, and become soft, flexible, and distorted. Also called
<altname>malacia</altname>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

